    <history>
      <narrative>Law 3-22, the “District of Columbia Smoking Restriction Act of 1979,” was introduced in Council and assigned Bill No. 3-109, which was referred to the Committee on Transportation and Environmental Affairs. The Bill was adopted on first and second readings on May 22, 1979 and June 19, 1979, respectively. Signed by the Mayor on July 12, 1979, it was assigned Act No. 3-66 and transmitted to both Houses of Congress for its review.</narrative>
